Class Experiment

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.projectcurie.Experiment
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Experiment
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class represents a database instance of a single experiment. It records the type of experiment, along with any metadata associated with it.

      • Experiment

        public Experiment(java.lang.String title,
                  java.lang.String description,
                  java.lang.String region,
                  int minTrialNumber,
                  boolean geolocationRequired,
                  java.lang.String owner,
                  com.example.projectcurie.ExperimentType type)
           throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Instantiate a new Experiment to be uploaded to the database.
        Parameters:
        title - The title of the experiment.
        description - A textual description of the experiment.
        region - A region in which trials are to take place.
        minTrialNumber - The minimum number of trials that must be submitted to this experiment.
        geolocationRequired - Indicates whether trials requires geolocation on behalf of the experimenter.
        owner - The username of the experiment's publisher.
        type - An enumeration that encodes the type of experiment (binomial, count, integer count, measurement).
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If any of the required fields are empty, throws an error.
